<TITLE> Iftekhar postpones launch of textbooks in Marma and Bom dialects </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bandarban, Aug 20 (bdnews24.com)  The launch of two textbooks in the Marma and Bom dialects could not be held Monday after Chittagong Hill Tracts affairs adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury postponed his visit to Bandarban. Bandarban district administration and the Tribal Cultural Institute authority confirmed the news. The adviser's office however said Iftekhar would visit Bandarban at a convenient time to launch the books. The textbooks for grade 1 have been written for the first time in the Marma and Bom languages. The adviser was also scheduled to exchange views with local reporters and inaugurate the Nilachal Tourist Centre during the visit. bdnews24.c
